<subSubSection id="C3776556ED113876FC9AFA59FEBBFEEC" lastPageId="579" lastPageNumber="580" pageId="576" pageNumber="577" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED113875FC9AFA59FC7DF8E6" blockId="576.[810,1452,1193,2070]" pageId="576" pageNumber="577">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED113875FC9AFA59FB9FFA70" bold="true" box="[863,1114,1431,1457]" pageId="576" pageNumber="577">Descriptionoffemale</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED113875FB75FA59FAE7FA73" box="[1200,1314,1431,1458]" captionStart="FIGURE 387" captionStartId="577.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[200,1352,219,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@577.[198,1388,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="577" captionText="FIGURE 387. Campopera caribbensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, caudal ramus; D, cephalic region, ventral; E, rostrum and antennules; F, antenna; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, 0.1 mm; C, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592090/files/figure.png" pageId="576" pageNumber="577">Fig. 387A</figureCitation>
) resembling that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED113875FC57FA74FB8CFA12" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[914,1097,1465,1492]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Campopera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="576" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magellanica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED113875FC57FA74FC60FA15" box="[914,933,1466,1492]" italics="true" pageId="576" pageNumber="577">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED113875FC7AFA77FB8CFA12" box="[959,1097,1465,1491]" italics="true" pageId="576" pageNumber="577">magellanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED113875FB98FA74FB06FA15" box="[1117,1219,1466,1492]" pageId="576" pageNumber="577" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED113875FB98FA74FB7BFA15" bold="true" box="[1117,1214,1466,1492]" pageId="576" pageNumber="577">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but segmentation of prosome more obscure. Body length 2.05 mm. Cephalosome indistinctly defined from metasome. Urosome 4-segmented (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED113875FB85F9D1FB7FF9FB" box="[1088,1210,1567,1594]" captionStart="FIGURE 387" captionStartId="577.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[200,1352,219,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@577.[198,1388,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="577" captionText="FIGURE 387. Campopera caribbensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, caudal ramus; D, cephalic region, ventral; E, rostrum and antennules; F, antenna; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, 0.1 mm; C, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592090/files/figure.png" pageId="576" pageNumber="577">Fig. 387B</figureCitation>
), distinctly narrower and shorter than prosome; first urosomite (genital complex) notarticulated from prosome; genital apertures not discernible. Three free abdominal somites indistinctly articulated. Caudalramus (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED113875FB91F969FB00F903" box="[1108,1221,1703,1730]" captionStart="FIGURE 387" captionStartId="577.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[200,1352,219,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@577.[198,1388,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="577" captionText="FIGURE 387. Campopera caribbensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, caudal ramus; D, cephalic region, ventral; E, rostrum and antennules; F, antenna; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, 0.1 mm; C, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592090/files/figure.png" pageId="576" pageNumber="577">Fig. 387C</figureCitation>
) small, lobate, about twiceaslongas wide (55×25 μm),fusiform, notarticulated from anal somite, ornamented with many setules: caudal setae absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED113877FC9AF8FEFE01F961" blockId="576.[810,1452,1193,2070]" lastBlockId="578.[136,778,1567,2070]" lastPageId="578" lastPageNumber="579" pageId="576" pageNumber="577">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED113875FC1DF8FEFBBBF88B" box="[984,1150,1840,1866]" captionStart="FIGURE 387" captionStartId="577.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[200,1352,219,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@577.[198,1388,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="577" captionText="FIGURE 387. Campopera caribbensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, caudal ramus; D, cephalic region, ventral; E, rostrum and antennules; F, antenna; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, 0.1 mm; C, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592090/files/figure.png" pageId="576" pageNumber="577">Fig. 387D, E</figureCitation>
) large, smooth, tapering in distal two-thirds towards rounded apex. Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED113875FCF7F8BAFC6DF84F" box="[818,936,1908,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 387" captionStartId="577.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[200,1352,219,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@577.[198,1388,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="577" captionText="FIGURE 387. Campopera caribbensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, caudal ramus; D, cephalic region, ventral; E, rostrum and antennules; F, antenna; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, 0.1 mm; C, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592090/files/figure.png" pageId="576" pageNumber="577">Fig. 387E</figureCitation>
) lobate, unsegmented, shorter than rostrum, blunt tipped, sparsely ornamented with minute setules over distal surface; setae apparently absent. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED113875FCF7F814FC63F835" box="[818,934,2010,2036]" captionStart="FIGURE 387" captionStartId="577.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[200,1352,219,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@577.[198,1388,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="577" captionText="FIGURE 387. Campopera caribbensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, caudal ramus; D, cephalic region, ventral; E, rostrum and antennules; F, antenna; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, 0.1 mm; C, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592090/files/figure.png" pageId="576" pageNumber="577">Fig. 387F</figureCitation>
) robust, 4-segmented; coxa, basis, and first endopodal segment unarmed, each much wider than long; distal endopodal segment about 1.4 times longerthan wide (45×33 μm): armedwith 4 smallsetae, 2 inserted into basal part of terminal claw; terminal claw strong, straight, aslongas segment.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF126655ED103874FF4DF8BDFC4CF813" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592090" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4592090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592090/files/figure.png" pageId="577" pageNumber="578" startId="577.[136,245,1907,1933]" targetBox="[200,1352,219,1842]" targetPageId="577">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED103874FF4DF8BDFC4CF813" blockId="577.[136,1452,1907,2003]" pageId="577" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED103874FF4DF8BDFEEBF84F" bold="true" box="[136,302,1907,1934]" pageId="577" pageNumber="578">FIGURE 387.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED103874FEF3F8BAFD81F84F" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[310,580,1908,1934]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Campopera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="577" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caribbensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED103874FEF3F8BAFD81F84F" box="[310,580,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="577" pageNumber="578">Campopera caribbensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED103874FD89F8BAFD62F84F" box="[588,679,1908,1934]" pageId="577" pageNumber="578" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED103874FD89F8BAFD67F84F" bold="true" box="[588,674,1908,1934]" pageId="577" pageNumber="578">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, caudal ramus; D, cephalic region, ventral; E, rostrum and antennules; F, antenna; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, 0.1 mm; C, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF126655ED133877FF4DFA77FA57FA15" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592092" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4592092" box="[136,1426,1465,1492]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592092/files/figure.png" pageId="578" pageNumber="579" startId="578.[136,245,1465,1491]" targetBox="[157,1416,210,1392]" targetPageId="578">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED133877FF4DFA77FA57FA15" blockId="578.[136,1426,1465,1492]" box="[136,1426,1465,1492]" pageId="578" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED133877FF4DFA77FEE8FA12" bold="true" box="[136,301,1465,1491]" pageId="578" pageNumber="579">FIGURE 388.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED133877FEF1FA74FD85FA12" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[308,576,1465,1492]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Campopera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="578" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caribbensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED133877FEF1FA74FD85FA12" box="[308,576,1465,1492]" italics="true" pageId="578" pageNumber="579">Campopera caribbensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED133877FD82FA74FD64FA15" box="[583,673,1466,1492]" pageId="578" pageNumber="579" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED133877FD82FA74FD59FA15" bold="true" box="[583,668,1466,1492]" pageId="578" pageNumber="579">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, female. A, leg 1; B, leg 2; C, leg 3; D, leg 4. Scale bars: 0.05 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED133877FF78F966FCB2F88A" blockId="578.[136,778,1567,2070]" lastBlockId="578.[810,1452,1567,2070]" pageId="578" pageNumber="579">
Labrum convex posteriorly. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED133877FD4CF966FCC7F903" box="[649,770,1704,1730]" captionStart="FIGURE 387" captionStartId="577.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[200,1352,219,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@577.[198,1388,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="577" captionText="FIGURE 387. Campopera caribbensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, caudal ramus; D, cephalic region, ventral; E, rostrum and antennules; F, antenna; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, 0.1 mm; C, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592090/files/figure.png" pageId="578" pageNumber="579">Fig. 387G</figureCitation>
) with broad coxal gnathobase bearing 3 major teeth and several minute denticles on medial margin, and bluntly produced, spinulose proximal corner; 3 major teeth each bearing 3 or 4 spinules on proximal margin; distalmost tooth with 1 minute denticle at base of distal margin: palp consisting of obscurely defined exopod bearing 5 short, naked setae and basis-endopod complex bearing 3 small, naked setae, one originating from basis region and remaining 2 more distally. Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED133877FD42F814FCC7F835" box="[647,770,2010,2036]" captionStart="FIGURE 387" captionStartId="577.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[200,1352,219,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@577.[198,1388,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="577" captionText="FIGURE 387. Campopera caribbensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, caudal ramus; D, cephalic region, ventral; E, rostrum and antennules; F, antenna; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, 0.1 mm; C, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592090/files/figure.png" pageId="578" pageNumber="579">Fig. 387H</figureCitation>
) bearing 8 setae on arthrite, 1 broad seta on coxal endite, 2 on epipodite; exopod and endopod fused with basis, bearing 4 setae each on exopodal region and endopodbasis complex; all setae pinnate. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED133877FAD0F9ADFA44F9BF" box="[1301,1409,1635,1662]" captionStart="FIGURE 387" captionStartId="577.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[200,1352,219,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@577.[198,1388,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="577" captionText="FIGURE 387. Campopera caribbensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, caudal ramus; D, cephalic region, ventral; E, rostrum and antennules; F, antenna; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, 0.1 mm; C, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592090/files/figure.png" pageId="578" pageNumber="579">Fig. 387I</figureCitation>
) 3- segmented; syncoxa bearing 2 endites, each tipped with 2 setae; basiswith 1 setaplusmassive clawbearing 2 rows of thick setules distally; endopod 1-segmented, rudimentary, tipped with 2 thin setae. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED133877FB1AF922FA88F8C7" box="[1247,1357,1772,1798]" captionStart="FIGURE 387" captionStartId="577.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[200,1352,219,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@577.[198,1388,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="577" captionText="FIGURE 387. Campopera caribbensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, caudal ramus; D, cephalic region, ventral; E, rostrum and antennules; F, antenna; G, mandible; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, 0.1 mm; C, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592090/files/figure.png" pageId="578" pageNumber="579">Fig. 387J</figureCitation>
) lobate, armed with 4 unequal, naked setae (2 subdistal and 2 distal).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED133876FC9AF89CFD49FECA" blockId="578.[810,1452,1567,2070]" lastBlockId="579.[136,778,173,574]" lastPageId="579" lastPageNumber="580" pageId="578" pageNumber="579">
Legs 1–4 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED133877FC1FF89CFBFFF8AD" box="[986,1082,1874,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 388" captionStartId="578.[136,245,1465,1491]" captionTargetBox="[157,1416,210,1392]" captionTargetId="figure-19@578.[136,1451,182,1410]" captionTargetPageId="578" captionText="FIGURE 388. Campopera caribbensis sp. nov., female. A, leg 1; B, leg 2; C, leg 3; D, leg 4. Scale bars: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592092/files/figure.png" pageId="578" pageNumber="579">Fig. 388</figureCitation>
A-D) biramous; both rami fused with protopod in all legs. Leg 1 with protopod retaining trace of articulation and bearing inner distal setaon basis region. Exopods of legs 1–4 larger than endopods. Exopod of leg 1 incompletely 2-segmented, but endopod and both rami of other legs unsegmented, lobate. Minute setae present: 6, 10, 7, and 5 on exopods of legs 1–4, respectively, and 4, 4 (or 5), 6, and 3 (or 4) on endopods of legs 1–4, respectively. Legs 5 and 6 absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED123876FF78FEDDFEBBFEEC" blockId="579.[136,778,173,574]" box="[189,382,275,301]" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED123876FF78FEDDFF3FFEEC" bold="true" box="[189,250,275,301]" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED123876FF78FEFBFD11FDFF" pageId="579" pageNumber="580" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED123876FF78FEFBFD11FDFF" blockId="579.[136,778,173,574]" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED123876FF78FEFBFEEDFE8E" bold="true" box="[189,296,309,335]" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED123876FEF9FEFBFD8CFE8E" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[316,585,309,335]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Campopera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="579" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caribbensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED123876FEF9FEFBFD8CFE8E" box="[316,585,309,335]" italics="true" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">Campopera caribbensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED123876FD93FEFBFD73FE8E" box="[598,694,309,335]" pageId="579" pageNumber="580" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED123876FD93FEFBFD6AFE8E" bold="true" box="[598,687,309,335]" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from itstwo congeners in havingan unsegmentedantennule compared to the 2-segmented limb present in both 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED123876FD35FEB7FECEFE74" baseAuthorityName="Schellenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1922" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Campopera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="579" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="michaelseni">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED123876FD35FEB7FCC7FE52" box="[752,770,377,403]" italics="true" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED123876FF4DFE55FECEFE74" box="[136,267,411,437]" italics="true" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">michaelseni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED123876FE97FE55FDC7FE74" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[338,514,411,437]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Campopera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="579" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magellanica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED123876FE97FE55FEA1FE74" box="[338,356,411,437]" italics="true" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED123876FEBFFE55FDC7FE74" box="[378,514,411,437]" italics="true" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">magellanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED123876FDD4FE55FDB6FE74" box="[529,627,411,437]" pageId="579" pageNumber="580" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED123876FDD4FE55FDA8FE74" bold="true" box="[529,621,411,437]" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
In addition, the maxillary syncoxa has 2 endites in the new species in contrast to 3 endites in both of its congeners, and the maxillary endopod has only 2 setae, in contrast to 3 setaein 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED123876FF4DFDEDFEEEFDFC" baseAuthorityName="Schellenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[136,299,547,574]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Campopera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="579" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="michaelseni">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED123876FF4DFDEDFF5FFDFC" box="[136,154,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED123876FF6DFDEDFEEEFDFC" box="[168,299,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">michaelseni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 4 setaein 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED123876FE08FDEDFDB0FDFC" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[461,629,547,574]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Campopera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="579" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magellanica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED123876FE08FDEDFE1AFDFC" box="[461,479,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED123876FE28FDEDFDB0FDFC" box="[493,629,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">magellanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED123876FDBEFDEDFD11FDFF" box="[635,724,547,574]" pageId="579" pageNumber="580" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED123876FDBEFDEDFD08FDFC" bold="true" box="[635,717,547,573]" pageId="579" pageNumber="580">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
